# Liabilities Other Financial Liabilities Deposits Placements Amount

## identifier
de7651

## type
float

## definition
This is the value of deposits and placements repayable by the reporting party as at the relevant date. Deposits are funds placed with the reporting party that are redeemable or withdrawable by the depositor. Placements are settlement account balances and items in the course of collection in relation to the payments system and security trades.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=credit
- name=Liabilities.OtherFinancialLiabilities.DepositsPlacements.Amount
- classification=baf/bafpo/bafpo6.02.06
- period=instant
